div.l:
For some say, at Dracanum; and some, on windy Icarus; and some, in Naxos, O Heaven-born, InsewnDionysus, after his untimely birth from Semele, was sewn into the thigh of Zeus.;
        and others by the deep-eddying river Alpheus that pregnant Semele bare you to Zeus the
        thunder-lover.
